        THE_TABS_YOU_ACQUIRE_CAN_BE_SPENT_ON                                  = 10946,  -- The tabs you acquire can be spent on field support.
        WHICH_ONE_YOU_HAVE_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_REPATRIATION                       = 10947,  -- Which one? (You have # [tab/tabs]). Nothing for now. Repatriation (#). White magic: Reraise (#). White magic: Regen (#). White magic: Refresh (#). White magic: Protect (#). White magic: Shell (#). Field recipe: Dried Meat (#). Field recipe: Salted Fish (#). Field recipe: Hard Cookie (#). Field recipe: Instant Noodles (#). Receive alter ego: Sakura. (#). Receive alter ego: Koru-Moru. (#).
        ARE_YOU_CERTAIN_YES_NO                                                = 10948,  -- Are you certain? Yes. No.
        RETURN_TO_YOUR_HOME_NATION_YES_NO                                     = 10949,  -- Return to your home nation? Yes. No.
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_TABS                                           = 10950,  -- You do not have enough tabs.
        IS_FULL_AND_CANNOT_EAT_ANYTHING_RIGHT_NOW                             = 10951,  -- % is full and cannot eat anything right now.
        YOU_MUST_WAIT_LONGER_BEFORE_YOU_ARE_ABLE                              = 10952,  -- You must wait longer before you are able to register a new training regime. It is recommended that you use this time to recuperate.
        WHICH_ONE_YOU_HAVE_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_READ                               = 10953,  -- Which one? (You have # [tab/tabs]). Nothing for now. Read instructions. %(#). %(#). %(#). %(#). %(#). %(#). %(#). %(#).
        ELITE_TRAINING_IS_A_SECTION_OF_THE_FIELD                              = 10954,  -- Elite training is a section of the Field Manual which caters to dauntless adventurers who wish to engage in a more grueling test of their mettle.
        TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_ELITE_TRAINING_REGIMES_YOU_MUST                     = 10955,  -- To participate in elite training regimes, you must acquire chapter transcripts, for which tabs are required.
        TRADING_GIL_OR_A_PIECE_OF_EQUIPMENT_AT                                = 10956,  -- Trading %, gil, or a piece of equipment at designated locations (while in possession of a chapter transcript) will trigger the commencement of your training.
        TRADED_ITEMS_WILL_NOT_BE_RETURNED_TO_YOU                              = 10957,  -- Traded items will not be returned to you. You will, however, be furnished with rewards of correlating value upon the successful completion of each elite training regime.
        EVEN_WITHIN_ELITE_TRAINING_THERE_ARE_REGIMES_OF                       = 10958,  -- Even within elite training, there are regimes of varying difficulty. The trade limit for each succeeding chapter will be greater than the last, and the training objective more challenging. For safety reasons, all participants are recommended to be well prepared.
        LASTLY_WE_AT_THE_A_M_A_N                                              = 10959,  -- Lastly, we at the A.M.A.N. recognize the importance of rest and recuperation as part of a healthy adventuring lifestyle. Therefore, a mandatory cool-down period will be imposed upon all adventurers following the completion of an elite training regime. Until this time has elapsed, you will be unable to undertake further training, even if a chapter transcript is in your possession.
        YOU_ALREADY_POSSESS                                                   = 10960,  -- You already possess %.
        YOU_CANNOT_UNDERTAKE_A_TRAINING_REGIME_WHILE_A                        = 10961,  -- You cannot undertake a training regime while a hunt is active.
        CANCEL_HUNT_YES_NO                                                    = 10962,  -- Cancel hunt? Yes. No.
        HUNT_CANCELED                                                         = 10963,  -- Hunt canceled.
        THE_REQUISITE_TIME_HAS_NOT_YET_ELAPSED_SINCE                          = 10964,  -- The requisite time has not yet elapsed since undertaking your last regime. You may be ineligible to receive gil and tab rewards.
        SET_TRAINING_REGIME_TO_AUTOMATICALLY_REPEAT_UPON_COMPLETION           = 10965,  -- Set training regime to automatically repeat upon completion?
        SET_TRAINING_REGIME_TO_REPEAT_YES_NO                                  = 10966,  -- Set training regime to repeat? Yes. No.
        YOU_VE_RECOVERED_ONE_OF_THE_LONG_LOST                                 = 10967,  -- You've recovered one of the long-lost mog tablets! You should share the news of your discovery with the Explorer Moogle in Ru'Lude Gardens.
        GREETINGS_ADVENTURER_YOU_VE_HEARD_THE_TALE_OF                         = 10968,  -- Greetings, adventurer! You've heard the tale of the mog tablets, haven't you? If any of them turn up in your travels, promise you'll let me know, kupo!
        MY_ADVENTURING_FRIEND_THANKS_TO_YOUR_EFFORTS_THE                      = 10969,  -- [Greetings/Happy Vana'versary], my adventuring friend! Thanks to your efforts, the mog tablets have been recovered, and their magic freed to spread happiness and joy across the realm! You are truly a friend to all mooglekind, kupo!
        OH_NO_WHAT_A_SHAME_KUPO_THE_MOG                                       = 10970,  -- Oh no! What a shame, kupo! The mog tablets that were recovered have been scattered to the ends of Vana'diel once more...
        ASK_ABOUT_SOMETHING_WHAT_S_A_MOG_TABLET                               = 10971,  -- Ask about something? What's a mog tablet? The history of mog tablets. List of tablets. Nothing.
        ASK_ABOUT_SOMETHING_WHAT_S_A_MOG_TABLET_2                             = 10972,  -- Ask about something? What's a mog tablet? The history of mog tablets. Collected tablets. The current Super Kupower. Nothing.
        ASK_ABOUT_SOMETHING_WHAT_S_A_MOG_TABLET_3                             = 10973,  -- Ask about something? What's a mog tablet? The history of mog tablets. Nothing.
        WHAT_S_A_MOG_TABLET_WHAT_S_A                                          = 10974,  -- What's a mog tablet!? What's a mog tablet, you say!? Why, only the most awesome, amazing artifact in the annals of moogle history, that's what, kupo!
        THERE_S_ELEVEN_OF_THEM_IN_ALL_TO                                      = 10975,  -- There's eleven of them in all, to be exact, scattered to the far reaches of Vana'diel and just waiting to be discovered by brave adventurers like you!
        WHAT_HAPPENS_IF_YOU_FIND_THEM_I_THOUGHT                               = 10976,  -- What happens if you find them? I thought you'd never ask, kupo! Each tablet is inscribed with an ancient moogle poem of joy, and legend has it that if all are found, the ancient moogle magic of King Kupofried the Great will be released once more, spreading joy and happiness through all the land!
        WE_EXPLORER_MOOGLES_HAVE_MADE_IT_OUR_LIFE                             = 10977,  -- We explorer moogles have made it our life's work to recover the tablets and unlock their powers. But with these short legs and little-bitty wings, we can't do it alone, kupo!
        THERE_I_VE_WHIPPED_UP_A_SPELL_THAT                                    = 10978,  -- There! I've whipped up a spell that will instantly transport any tablets you find back here to me. Come back if you find anything, and happy exploring, kupo!
        JUST_SIT_RIGHT_BACK_AND_I_LL_TELL                                     = 10979,  -- Just sit right back and I'll tell you the tale, kupo. Many, many ages past, we moogles had our own glorious kingdom. It was truly the peak of moogle civilization, a veritable golden age for all mooglekind!
        THE_SEVENTH_KING_OF_THIS_GREAT_NATION_WAS                             = 10980,  -- The seventh king of this great nation was the wise and kindly King Kupofried, a masterful magician famed as the father of the fantastic moogle magic that survives to this very day, kupo!
        IN_HIS_LATER_YEARS_KING_KUPOFRIED_EMBARKED_ON                         = 10981,  -- In his later years, King Kupofried embarked on what would become the greatest work of his illustrious reign. Seeking to pass down the prosperity of his kingdom to future generations, he inscribed eleven incantations of moogle joy and happiness onto eleven stone tablets.
        SADLY_THE_KINDLY_KING_S_INTENTIONS_WENT_UNAPPRECIATED                 = 10982,  -- Sadly, the kindly king's intentions went unappreciated by his selfish sons and daughters, and many a fierce feud broke out over who would inherit these relics, kupo...
        KING_KUPOFRIED_WAS_GREATLY_DISMAYED_HOW_COULD_THE                     = 10983,  -- King Kupofried was greatly dismayed. How could the poems that he had composed out of pure love and joy become the root of such strife?
        IN_HIS_DESPAIR_THE_KING_COMMANDED_HIS_MINION                          = 10984,  -- In his despair, the king commanded his minion bats to scatter the tablets to the far corners of the world, where they would be seen by moogle eyes no more.
        ALAS_I_ONLY_WANTED_MY_CHILDREN_TO_BE                                  = 10985,  -- Alas! I only wanted my children to be happy, kupo, he lamented, and flew away on his tiny yet majestic wings, never to be seen in his kingdom again.
        LEFT_WITHOUT_ITS_WISE_MONARCH_THE_ONCE_GLORIOUS                       = 10986,  -- Left without its wise monarch, the once-glorious moogle kingdom fractured into warring tribes, falling into unrest...and, eventually, ruin. A tragic tale, don't you think, kupo?
        WE_EXPLORER_MOOGLES_ARE_THE_PROUD_DESCENDANTS_OF                      = 10987,  -- We explorer moogles are the proud descendants of King Kupofried, living only to bring our last great monarch's unrealized dream to fruition. We will--we must!--find the mog tablets and bring true joy and happiness to this world!
        LET_S_SEE_IT_APPEARS_THAT_MOOGLE_ALREADY                              = 10988,  -- Let's see... It appears that # moogle [tablet has/tablets have] already been found, kupo.
        HERE_S_A_LIST_OF_ALL_THE_LOCATED                                      = 10989,  -- Here's a list of all the located tablets, kupo!
        CHOOSE_A_LOCATION_WEST_RONFAURE_EAST_RONFAURE_LA                      = 10990,  -- Choose a location: West Ronfaure. East Ronfaure. La Theine Plateau. Valkurm Dunes. Jugner Forest. Batallia Downs. North Gustaberg. South Gustaberg. Konschtat Highlands. Pashhow Marshlands. Rolanberry Fields. Beaucedine Glacier. Xarcabard. West Sarutabaruta. East Sarutabaruta. Tahrongi Canyon. Buburimu Peninsula. Meriphataud Mountains. Sauromugue Champaign. Qufim Island. Behemoth's Dominion. Cape Teriggan. Eastern Altepa Desert. The Sanctuary of Zi'Tah. Ro'Maeve. Yuhtunga Jungle. Yhoator Jungle. Western Altepa Desert. Valley of Sorrows. Cancel.
        THE_TABLET_OF_WAS_DISCOVERED_THERE_BY_KUPO                            = 10991,  -- The tablet of [temperance/fortitude/piety/justice/hope/wisdom/compassion/dignity/loyalty/charity/courage] was discovered there by %, kupo!
        THE_TABLET_OF_WAS_DISCOVERED_THERE_KUPO                               = 10992,  -- The tablet of [temperance/fortitude/piety/justice/hope/wisdom/compassion/dignity/loyalty/charity/courage] was discovered there, kupo!
        NO_TABLET_HAS_BEEN_DISCOVERED_THERE_YET_IT                            = 10993,  -- No tablet has been discovered there yet. It's not too late for you to stake your claim, kupo!
        OH_GLORIOUS_DAY_ALL_ELEVEN_MOG_TABLETS_HAVE                           = 10994,  -- Oh, glorious day! All eleven mog tablets have been recovered and restored to their rightful place at the altar of King Kupofried!
        CAN_YOU_FEEL_THE_ANCIENT_MOOGLE_MAGIC_IN                              = 10995,  -- Can you feel the ancient moogle magic in the air? You can now bask in the benefits of this Super Kupower...
        THRIFTY_TRANSIT_A_SPECIAL_TREAT_FOR_THE_COST                          = 10996,  -- Thrifty Transit! A special treat for the cost-conscious adventurer! For a limited time, all survival guide costs are eliminated, and you are able to teleport between nearby cities for a small fee, kupo!
        MARTIAL_MASTER_AS_AN_ADDED_BONUS_TO_YOUR                              = 10997,  -- Martial Master! As an added bonus to your Signet, combat skills will increase more rapidly! Your magic and automaton skills will be boosted, too!
        BLOOD_OF_THE_VAMPYR_SIGNETS_HAVE_BEEN_BOOSTED                         = 10998,  -- Blood of the Vampyr! Signets have been boosted with the abilities of Regeneration and Refresh!
        TREASURE_HOUND_WITH_SIGNET_IN_EFFECT_YOU_WILL                         = 10999,  -- Treasure Hound! With Signet in effect, you will now be able to sniff out more treasure and gil! Great riches surely await you, kupo!
        ARTISAN_S_ADVANTAGE_GOOD_NEWS_FOR_ASPIRING_ARTISANS                   = 11000,  -- Artisan's Advantage! Good news for aspiring artisans, kupo! When receiving advanced image support, the chance of your ingredients being lost in a failed synthesis attempt has been drastically reduced!
        MYRIAD_MYSTERY_BOXES_WHAT_S_THIS_KUPO_MYSTERIOUS                      = 11001,  -- Myriad Mystery Boxes! What's this, kupo? Mysterious boxes have been sighted all over the realm! What genius could have devised such commendable creations?
        DILATORY_DIGESTION_NOT_CONTENT_TO_BE_LEFT_BEHIND                      = 11002,  -- Dilatory Digestion! Not content to be left behind, brown magic slides back out for another go, kupo! Now you can be what you eat for twice as long and save on all those trips to your local merchant.
        BOUNDARY_BUSTER_TRUST_IN_SIGNET_AND_YOU_CAN                           = 11003,  -- Boundary Buster! Trust in Signet and you can never go wrong, kupo! It's time to take to the field and vanquish a veritable army of enemies, for any Conquest Points you receive will be duly doubled!
        BOUNTIFUL_BAZAAR_TRADE_ROUTES_ARE_BUSTLING_WITH_UNPRECEDENTED         = 11004,  -- Bountiful Bazaar! Trade routes are bustling with unprecedented traffic and peddlers' carts are overflowing with objects now that regional goods are available to merchants across the realm, kupo!
        SWIFT_SHOES_THIS_IS_JUST_THE_TICKET_FOR                               = 11005,  -- Swift Shoes! This is just the ticket for today's busy adventurer! For a limited time, provided that you're fully rested and healed, your legs will carry you with the speed of a chocobo!
        CRYSTAL_CABOODLE_SIGNET_IS_NOW_BETTER_THAN_EVER                       = 11006,  -- Crystal Caboodle! Signet is now better than ever! Collect crystals from beastmen-controlled areas...and maybe even clusters from other areas!
        BE_WARNED_THAT_OUR_MOOGLE_MAGIC_IS_CONCENTRATED                       = 11008,  -- Be warned that our moogle magic is concentrated around this altar. If you venture to far-off lands, the Super Kupowers will be unable to protect you...
        WHAT_WHAT_ABOUT_THE_PAST_YOU_SAY_OF                                   = 11009,  -- What? What about the past, you say? Of course the magic won't travel through time. What a strange question, kupo...
        BUT_NOT_AN_ALTOGETHER_POINTLESS_ONE_THE_POWERS                        = 11010,  -- But not an altogether pointless, one. The powers of thirtfy transit do seem to apply across the space-time continuum, kupo.
        THE_WHOLE_SYSTEM_IS_FILLED_WITH_MYSTERIES                             = 11011,  -- The whole system is filled with mysteries.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_IT_S_REALLY_YOU                                           = 11012,  -- Oh, it's you! It's really you! The brave adventurer who discovered one of our mog tablets!
        IT_S_A_PLEASURE_AN_HONOR_TO_MEET                                      = 11013,  -- It's a pleasure, an honor to meet you, kupo! We have a special prize to reward you for your efforts. If you'll just sign right here...
        SIGN_FOR_THE_MOOGLE_SURE_I_DON_T                                      = 11014,  -- Sign for the moogle? Sure. I don't think so.
        OH_THANK_YOU_MISTER_MISS_A_TRULY_HEROIC                               = 11015,  -- Oh, thank you, Mister/Miss]...%! A truly heroic name, kupo!
        AS_A_REWARD_FOR_YOUR_EFFORTS_PLEASE_HAVE                              = 11016,  -- As a reward for your efforts, please have this! Many thanks, and [safe travels/Happy Vana'versary], kupo!
        WHAT_YOU_WON_T_THAT_S_A_SHAME                                         = 11017,  -- What? You won't? That's a shame, kupo. I had a special prize here just for you, but without your signature, I'll just have to hold on to it...
        IF_YOU_CHANGE_YOUR_MIND_COME_BACK_QUICKLY                             = 11018,  -- If you change your mind, come back quickly. The mog tablets will be scattered to the wind again at any moment, kupo...
        F_TH_FTH_FON_U                                                        = 11019,  -- F<tH[ FtH[ %FoN;u
        FWOI_XQ_FO_AUK_FKOX_XO_FLOX_XO                                        = 11020,  -- FWOi[XQ Fo^#AuK FkOX^xO FlOX^xO
        FRV_BGN_FPV_NE_FX_KN_F_XFBXM                                          = 11021,  -- FRV%^bgn FpV%nE@ Fx#[kn F{XfBXM
        FUJO_H_F_T_O_FT_O_F                                                   = 11022,  -- FUJo[h F<T^o^ FT^o^ F^M%e,J
        FUU_F_T_GRN_F_OL_FNTB                                                 = 11023,  -- Fuu#< F#t@gRn F\Ol FNtB
        LJ_H_FE_K_FAEP_F9NWE                                                  = 11024,  -- %Lj#h Fe#K& FAep;F9nWE^
        FE_F_K_EXQ_F_AG_EXQ_F                                                 = 11025,  -- FE[ F^K%eXQ F%Ag%eXQ F<Aep;1
        TIMESTAMPF                                                            = 11027,  -- TimeStampF
        STEP_HJ_SUBSTEPF                                                      = 11028,  -- step%hj substepF
        A_B                                                                   = 11029,  -- A: B:
        ID_11034                                                              = 11034,  -- ====
        CODEF                                                                 = 11035,  -- codeF
        TIMEWORKF_TIMENOW_F_TIMELASTFSEC                                      = 11036,  -- TIMEWORKF TIMENOW F TIMELASTFSec.
        HI_THERE_I_M_YOUR_FRIENDLY_NEIGHBORHOOD_SMILE                         = 11037,  -- Hi there! I'm your friendly neighborhood smile sergeant! I'm in charge of running the [beginner/intermediate/advanced] level Smilebringer Boot Camp in this area.
        I_D_BE_THRILLED_TO_ANSWER_ANY_QUESTIONS                               = 11038,  -- I'd be thrilled to answer any questions you might have...and of course, sign you up, too! You'd like that, wouldn't you? Hmmm?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_UNDERTAKE_TRAINING_HEAR_AN                           = 11039,  -- What will you do? Undertake training. Hear an explanation. What's the qualifying time? What's the fastest time? Nothing.
        FANTASTIC_BUT_OH_IT_SEEMS_YOU_DON_T                                   = 11040,  -- Fantastic! But, oh...it seems you don't have %. Well, that's just too bad!
        IT_D_BE_MY_PLEASURE_HERE_GOES_NOTHING                                 = 11041,  -- It'd be my pleasure! Here goes nothing! Ahem! The Smilebringer Boot Camp was established for two purposes, the first being the ongoing training and conditioning of smilebringers. The second--and this is where you come in, yay!--is for us to scout hopefuls from the adventurer community to join our jovial ranks!
        THE_POPULATION_OF_VICIOUS_MONSTERS_HAS_GROWN_IN                       = 11042,  -- The population of vicious monsters has grown in recent years, you see. And because of this, more smilebringers were being--<gasp!>--injured in the line of duty than ever before.
        BUT_WE_WEREN_T_GOING_TO_TAKE_THAT                                     = 11043,  -- But we weren't going to take that sitting down, no siree. The day we smilebringers stop doing our job--that is, bringing smiles--is the day the world ends!
        WHATEVER_THE_PREDICAMENT_AND_NO_MATTER_THE_SIZE                       = 11044,  -- Whatever the predicament, and no matter the size of the ruszor-inflicted gash wound, we will--we must--pull through...for the sake of the children!
        WITH_THESE_HEART_WARMING_IDEALS_IN_MIND_THE                           = 11045,  -- With these heart-warming ideals in mind, the Smilebringer Boot Camp was established. Ta-da! Smilebringers graduating from this camp are better equipped to meet the ever-changing needs of these unstable times we live in.
        THE_RULES_ARE_AS_SIMPLE_AS_SUNSHINE_SMILEBRINGER                      = 11046,  -- The rules are as simple as sunshine. Smilebringer's honor! When I give you the word, run to each of the checkpoints we've set up in the area. Smile helpers are posted at each, so you can't miss them!
        TALK_TO_THE_SMILE_HELPERS_AND_THEY_LL                                 = 11047,  -- Talk to the smile helpers and they'll confirm your passage. The route you take is completely up to you--just be sure you don't miss any checkpoints. You got all that? Hmmm?
        I_LL_MARK_EACH_SMILE_HELPER_S_LOCATION                                = 11048,  -- I'll mark each smile helper's location on your map beforehand, so you don't need to worry about getting lost.
        ONCE_YOU_VE_FINISHED_VISITING_ALL_THE_CHECKPOINTS                     = 11049,  -- Once you've finished visiting all the checkpoints, you have to--you guessed it!--come back and report to me. It's okay, I won't bite!
        WHAT_I_WILL_DO_THOUGH_IS_TELL_YOU                                     = 11050,  -- What I will do, though, is tell you how quickly you completed the course. After all, to a smilebringer, speed is everything. Some folks run faster with a fell beast hot on their tail, but we smilebringers need no more than the thought of a child's laughter to spur us on! Zoom zoom!
        OH_AND_I_SHOULD_MENTION_THAT_AT_THIS                                  = 11051,  -- Oh, and I should mention that at this time of year, we're collecting donations in the form of a small fee to participate in the training. All proceeds go towards presents for the children during the Starlight Celebration. Thank you for your cooperation!
        ONE_MORE_THING_YOU_SHOULD_KNOW_IF_YOU                                 = 11052,  -- One more thing you should know. If you venture out of the area, the training will automatically be canceled. But I can trust you not to walk out on your favorite smile sergeant, right? Hmmm?
        SO_FAR_THE_FASTEST_TIME_IN_THIS_AREA                                  = 11053,  -- So far, the fastest time in this area is # minute[/s] # second[/s]. Wow! And the name of the greased lightning who set this record is %. Don't be forgetting that, you hear?
        WE_D_LIKE_ALL_PARTICIPANTS_TO_COMPLETE_THIS                           = 11054,  -- We'd like all participants to complete this area's course within # minute[/s] # second[/s]. A piece of cake for a strapping young wolf/vixen] like you, surely! And if you manage a time quicker than # minute[/s] # second[/s]...then you and I had better trade places! Oh, that would be so much fun, wouldn't it?
        AWWW_YOU_VE_MADE_THIS_SMILE_SERGEANT_VERY                             = 11055,  -- Awww... You've made this smile sergeant very sad... But I'll be glued to this spot, because I just know you'll be back to turn my frown upside down! Yes siree!
        AT_THIS_TIME_OF_YEAR_WE_RE_COLLECTING                                 = 11056,  -- At this time of year, we're collecting a donation of # gil from each participant. All proceeds go towards presents for the children. Oh, won't you think of the children? <Sniffle>...
        GIVE_TO_THE_CHILDREN_I_LIVE_TO_GIVE                                   = 11057,  -- Give to the children? I live to give! Charity begins at home.
        BUT_OF_COURSE_FIRST_I_LL_NEED_YOU                                     = 11058,  -- But of course! First, I'll need you to lend me your %... Oh, don't pout! I'll give it back as soon as I'm done, promise!
        YOU_LL_FIND_EACH_OF_THE_TEN_SMILE                                     = 11059,  -- You'll find each of the ten smile helpers by the points I've indicated. Don't forget to talk with every one of them or it won't count, okay?
        THERE_I_VE_MARKED_EACH_SMILE_HELPER_S                                 = 11060,  -- There! I've marked each smile helper's location for you. If you ever lose your bearings in the middle of a run, just open up your map and everything will be aaall right. Trust me! <Wink>
        SO_ARE_YOU_READY_STEADY_LEVEL_TRAINING_GO                             = 11061,  -- So, are you ready-steady? [Beginner/Intermediate/Advanced] level training...GO! Come on, pump those legs like there's no tomorrow!
        SINCE_THE_STARLIGHT_CELEBRATION_HAS_ENDED_WE_VE                       = 11062,  -- Since the Starlight Celebration has ended, we've had to make a few changes.
        BUT_THE_SMILEBRINGER_BOOT_CAMP_WILL_BE_AVAILABLE                      = 11063,  -- But the Smilebringer Boot Camp will be available for off-season conditioning the whole year round, so come back whenever you're in the mood. I'll be waiting for you!
        OH_YOU_RE_BACK_I_WAS_AFRAID_WE                                        = 11064,  -- Oh, you're back! I was afraid we'd lost you to some foul creature prowling the wilderness. Let's start from the top, shall we?
        OH_WHAT_RE_YOU_DOING_HERE_AREN_T                                      = 11065,  -- Oh, what're you doing here? Aren't you in the middle of a run right now? Couldn't stand to be parted from your favorite smile sergeant, maybe? Teehee!
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_HEAR_AN_EXPLANATION_WHERE                            = 11066,  -- What will you do? Hear an explanation. Where're the smile helpers again? Cancel the training. Nothing.
        AWWW_THESE_RIVULETS_OF_TEARS_STREAMING_DOWN_MY                        = 11067,  -- Awww... These rivulets of tears streaming down my face... B-but it's okay... You have your own reasons for quitting, and I understand... <Sob>
        WELCOME_BACK_LET_S_CHECK_YOUR_TIME_SHALL                              = 11068,  -- Welcome back! Let's check your time, shall we? You cleared the course in # minute[/s] # second[/s].
        OH_MY_GODDESS_YOU_VE_SET_A_NEW                                        = 11069,  -- Oh my Goddess! You've set a new record for this area! Hooray! Somebody, break out the fireworks!
        YOU_VE_SUCCESSFULLY_QUALIFIED_YAY_HERE_S_A                            = 11070,  -- You've successfully qualified! Yay! Here's a little something to commemorate this marvelous achievement.
        YOU_OBTAIN_3                                                          = 11071,  -- You obtain %!
        AH_JUST_THE_KNOWLEDGE_THAT_THERE_RE_CAPABLE                           = 11072,  -- Ah, just the knowledge that there're capable adventurers like you around helps me sleep better at night. The children...they're in good hands... <Sob>
        YOU_DID_JUST_FINE_BUT_DON_T_BE                                        = 11073,  -- You did just fine, but don't be resting on those laurels, you hear? As we smilebringers say, there's always a bigger, brighter smile to be had!
        OH_NO_I_M_AFRAID_YOUR_TIME_FALLS                                      = 11074,  -- Oh no! I'm afraid your time falls short of qualification! As much as I want to give you a passing grade, headquarters wouldn't let me hear the end of it.
        OH_NO_PLEASE_DON_T_BE_MAD_BUT                                         = 11075,  -- Oh no! Please don't be mad, but...I forgot to record your time. I hope you'll find it in your heart to forgive this scatterbrain of a smile sergeant...
        IT_MIGHT_SURPRISE_YOU_TO_LEARN_THIS_BUT                               = 11076,  -- It might surprise you to learn this, but even the toughest--grrrrrr!--and roughest of us smilebringers need rest and relaxation. Oh, wipe that grin off your face! I knew you wouldn't believe me!
        AAANYWAY_WHAT_I_MEANT_TO_SAY_IS_WORK                                  = 11077,  -- Aaanyway! What I meant to say is, work hard, play hard is our motto, and it applies to boot camp participants, too. After you complete a run with a qualifying time--yay!--you're required to rest up until the next day (Vana'diel time).
        AWWW_SEEING_THE_WAY_YOU_RE_SIMPLY_BURSTING                            = 11078,  -- Awww, seeing the way you're simply bursting with enthusiasm makes me want to cry tears of joy. But you have to be cruel to be kind. No more training until tomorrow, young man/lady]! No siree!
        DEBUG_MESSAGES                                                        = 11079,  -- Debug Messages.
        ALL_CHECKPOINTS_SWITCHED_ON_PARTICIPATION_XMAS_OFF                    = 11080,  -- All checkpoints switched ON. Participation: # Xmas: # OFF: #
        ELAPSED_TIME_MIN_AND_SEC                                              = 11081,  -- Elapsed time: # min and # sec.
        CHANGE_EVENT_MODE_STARLIGHT_CELEBRATION_OFF_SEASON_EVENT              = 11082,  -- Change event mode. Starlight Celebration. Off-season. Event off.
        CHECKPOINT_CLEARED_ELAPSED_TIME_MINUTE_SECOND                         = 11083,  -- Checkpoint ## cleared! Elapsed time: # minute[/s] # second[/s]
        CHECKPOINT_CLEARED_YOU_GAIN_THE_EFFECT_OF_FLEE                        = 11084,  -- Checkpoint ## cleared! You gain the effect of Flee. Elapsed time: # minute[/s] # second[/s]
        YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_CLEARED_THIS_CHECKPOINT_ELAPSED_TIME                 = 11085,  -- You have already cleared this checkpoint. Elapsed time: # minute[/s] # second[/s]
        ELAPSED_TIME_MINUTE_SECOND                                            = 11086,  -- Elapsed time: # minute[/s] # second[/s]
        ALL_CHECKPOINTS_CLEARED_PLEASE_REPORT_BACK_TO_THE                     = 11087,  -- All checkpoints cleared! Please report back to the smile sergeant in charge.
        TARGET_OUT_OF_RANGE_2                                                 = 11088,  -- Target out of range.
        THIS_IS_A_CHECKPOINTARU_FOR_THE_SMILEBRINGER_BOOT                     = 11089,  -- This is a checkpointaru for the Smilebringer Boot Camp. To learny-wearn more, please speak with the smile sergeant posted by the [town entrance/telepointaru].
        YOU_OBTAIN_4                                                          = 11090,  -- You obtain % !
        IF_I_WERE_YOU_I_D_STEP_AWAY                                           = 11091,  -- If I were you, I'd step away from that thing.
        HM_THAT_YOU_GOT_THERE_WELL_THEN_THAT                                  = 11092,  -- Hm? That % you got there... Well then, that makes you %.
        MY_NAME_S_ORGIS_AN_I_M_A                                              = 11093,  -- My name's Orgis, an' I'm a friend of Joachim's. I've heard much about the invaluable aid you've lent to our cause.
        EVEN_HAVIN_SEEN_THE_STATE_OF_OUR_WORLD                                = 11094,  -- Even havin' seen the state of our world, you keep on comin' back, over an' over. I'd say you're curious to a fault, mate. Either that, or you've got morbid tastes, I reckon.
        FUNNY_ENOUGH_THAT_S_EXACTLY_THE_KIND_OF                               = 11095,  -- Funny enough, that's exactly the kind of spirit Abyssea wants for right now.
        JUS_SO_YOU_KNOW_THE_CAVERNOUS_MAW_YOU                                 = 11096,  -- Jus' so you know, the cavernous maw you see here won't take you to the South Gustaberg of Abyssea.
        STEP_ON_THROUGH_AN_YOU_LL_FIND_YOURSELF                               = 11097,  -- Step on through, an' you'll find yourself standin' on the vast sands of the Altepa Desert. Yep, all the way over on Zepwell Island. All adventurers worth their salt would've been there a time or three. Don't know 'bout you, though.
        WORD_IS_THIS_DISCREPANCY_BETWEEN_ENTRANCE_AN_EXIT                     = 11098,  -- Word is, this discrepancy between entrance an' exit occurs with certain maws.
        SOMETHIN_TO_DO_WITH_DIMENSIONAL_MISALIGNMENT_BUT_THAT                 = 11099,  -- Somethin' to do with dimensional misalignment, but that scientific stuff's waaay over my head.
        JUS_KNOWIN_WHERE_A_PARTICULAR_MAW_IS_GONNA                            = 11100,  -- Jus' knowin' where a particular maw is gonna take me is plenty, I reckon.
        BUT_GETTIN_BACK_ON_TOPIC_IT_S_BLEEDIN                                 = 11101,  -- But gettin' back on topic. It's bleedin' obvious you're dyin' to throw yourself into this maw, so I won't keep you long.
        IT_S_A_WELL_KNOWN_FACT_THAT_FOLK                                      = 11102,  -- It's a well-known fact that folk of your world gain great powers when you set foot in our world, an' boy are we jealous!
        THAT_SAID_THERE_S_ONE_PIECE_OF_INFORMATION                            = 11103,  -- That said, there's one piece of information you oughta take with you...somethin' that jus' might save your hide, I reckon.
        AN_OVERGROWN_ROC_HAS_BEEN_TERRORIZIN_THE_FOLK                         = 11104,  -- An overgrown roc has been terrorizin' the folk of the desert. Size isn't the creature's only claim to notoriety, though.
        IF_THE_TALES_RE_TRUE_IT_S_ALSO                                        = 11105,  -- If the tales're true, it's also as quick as a flash, an' can kick up a fierce storm simply in the wake of its passage.
        I_KNOW_A_BUNCH_OF_POOR_SODS_WHO                                       = 11106,  -- I know a bunch of poor sods who had a run-in with the beast. They managed to shamble back to camp somehow, but not before...before most o' their skin 'ad been flayed off. Gore galore, I tell you.
        ALTEPA_IS_RIGHT_INFESTED_WITH_SWARMS_OF_SAVAGE                        = 11107,  -- Altepa is right infested with swarms of savage fiends, but this roc looms heads an' shoulders above the rest. Stay away from the fiend if you value your skin--literally.
        IF_WE_COULD_SOMEHOW_DO_AWAY_WITH_THE                                  = 11108,  -- If we could somehow do away with the hellish beast...but that's jus' some fool's dream. Might as well wait for hell to freeze over, or the skies to turn blue again, I reckon.
        NOW_JUS_ONE_LAST_THING_BEFORE_I_LET                                   = 11109,  -- Now, jus' one last thing before I let you go. Your ears are probably bent beyond repair from hearin' these words, but I feel obliged to say 'em to you anyway: my folk an' I are countin' on you.
        AH_YOU_RE_BACK_SEEMS_THERE_S_MORE                                     = 11110,  -- Ah, you're back. Seems there's more to you than meets the eye, mate.
        EVEN_BEFORE_WE_TALKED_I_D_HEARD_ABOUT                                 = 11111,  -- Even before we talked, I'd heard about your dauntless feats, but it never crossed my mind that you might be the one to eliminate that terrible menace.
        THANKS_TO_YOU_THE_SURVIVORS_IN_ALTEPA_NOW                             = 11112,  -- Thanks to you, the survivors in Altepa now dare to dream of better days ahead.
        I_VE_BROUGHT_A_LIL_SOMETHIN_FOR_YOU                                   = 11113,  -- I've brought a lil' somethin' for you, to help you on your way.
        IT_S_SOMETHIN_THAT_S_SUPPOSED_TO_WORK                                 = 11114,  -- It's %, somethin' that's supposed to work like a charm for folk of your world.
        IT_S_A_BLOODY_HARD_VARIETY_OF_THE                                     = 11115,  -- It's a bloody hard variety of the stone to come by, so don't go losin' it, eh?
        SIGH_EACH_TIME_I_STEP_INTO_TRANQUIL_VANA                              = 11116,  -- <Sigh>... Each time I step into tranquil Vana'diel, it feels as though I'm wakin' up from a bad dream. If only that were the case, eh?
        AN_SPEAKIN_OF_THE_DEVIL_LOOKS_LIKE_MY                                 = 11117,  -- An' speakin' of the devil, looks like my time's up. As much as I'd love to stay around an' chat, I've gotta get back to my livin' nightmare.
        MY_MATES_AN_I_HAVE_HIGH_HOPES_FOR                                     = 11118,  -- My mates an' I have high hopes for you, %. Don't let us down, eh?
        YOU_ARE_TOO_FAR_AWAY_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN                                = 11119,  -- You are too far away to participate in the Voidwatch operation.
        YOU_ARE_CURRENTLY_ENGAGED_ELSEWHERE_AND_CANNOT_PARTICIPATE            = 11120,  -- You are currently engaged elsewhere and cannot participate in the Voidwatch operation.
        YOU_ARE_UNCONSCIOUS_AND_CANNOT_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE                     = 11121,  -- You are unconscious and cannot participate in the Voidwatch operation.
        YOU_DO_NOT_FULFILL_THE_REQUIREMENTS_TO_PARTICIPATE                    = 11122,  -- You do not fulfill the requirements to participate in the Voidwatch operation.
        GAINS_CLEARANCE_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION             = 11123,  -- % gains clearance to participate in the Voidwatch operation. One % expended.
        GAINS_CLEARANCE_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION_2           = 11124,  -- % gains clearance to participate in the Voidwatch operation. % not expended. (Spoils will be subject to limits.)
        GAINS_CLEARANCE_TO_PARTICIPATE_IN_THE_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION_3           = 11125,  -- % gains clearance to participate in the Voidwatch operation. Unused % carried over.
        YOU_HAVE_VENTURED_TOO_FAR_FROM_THE_FIELD_3                            = 11126,  -- You have ventured too far from the field of battle. You will be automatically relieved of Voidwatcher status if you do not return.
        YOU_HAVE_VENTURED_TOO_FAR_FROM_THE_FIELD_4                            = 11127,  -- You have ventured too far from the field of battle. Voidwatcher status revoked.
        YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_TO_THE_FIELD_OF_BATTLE_2                            = 11128,  -- You have returned to the field of battle.
        YOU_HAVE_EARTH_TIME_TO_COMPLETE_THE_BATTLE_2                          = 11129,  -- You have # [minute/minutes] (Earth time) to complete the battle.
        YOU_HAVE_EARTH_TIME_REMAINING_TO_COMPLETE_THE_2                       = 11130,  -- You have # [minute/minutes] (Earth time) remaining to complete the battle.
        YOU_HAVE_ONLY_EARTH_TIME_REMAINING_2                                  = 11131,  -- You have only # [second/seconds] (Earth time) remaining.
        YOUR_TIME_FOR_THIS_BATTLE_IS_UP                                       = 11132,  -- Your time for this battle is up...
        THE_MONSTER_FADES_BEFORE_YOUR_EYES_A_LOOK_2                           = 11133,  -- The monster fades before your eyes, a look of disappointment on its face.
        TEMPORARY_ITEM_IS_AVAILABLE_FOR_USE                                   = 11134,  -- Temporary item: % is available for use!
        ALL_TEMPORARY_ITEMS_ARE_RECHARGED                                     = 11135,  -- All temporary items are recharged!
        YOU_FEEL_A_MYSTERIOUS_ENERGY_SEEPING_FORTH_FROM                       = 11136,  -- You feel a mysterious energy seeping forth from an unknown source...
        THE_RESONATES_WITH_THE_YOU_MAY_COMMENCE_THE                           = 11137,  -- The % resonates with the %. You may commence the Voidwatch operation at will.
        A_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION_COULD_BE_INITIATED_IF_ONLY                      = 11138,  -- A Voidwatch operation could be initiated if only you had % and %...
        HOWEVER_YOUR_PRESENCE_DOES_NOT_SEEM_TO_ELICIT                         = 11139,  -- However, your presence does not seem to elicit a reaction.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_INITIATE_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION                 = 11140,  -- What will you do? Nothing. Initiate Voidwatch operation. View alignment values. Examine atmacite. Read up on the Voidwatch.
        USE_YES_NO                                                            = 11141,  -- Use %? Yes. No.
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_THE_NECESSARY_TO_INITIATE                          = 11142,  -- You do not possess the % necessary to initiate a Voidwatch operation here.
        A_FIEND_MATERIALIZES_FROM_THE_PLANAR_RIFT                             = 11143,  -- A fiend materializes from the planar rift!
        CURRENT_SPECTRAL_ALIGNMENT_BLUE_REWARD_QUANTITY_RED_REWARD            = 11144,  -- Current Spectral Alignment Blue: +#% (reward quantity) Red: +#% (reward quality)
        YELLOW_EXPERIENCE_YIELD_GREEN_CRUOR_YIELD                             = 11145,  -- Yellow: +#% (experience yield) Green: +#% (cruor yield)
        ALIGNMENT_BONUSES_GRANTED_BY_ASCENT_ITEMS_WILL_BE                     = 11146,  -- Alignment bonuses granted by ascent items will be added to the final value.
        YOU_CAN_INFUSE_UP_TO_ATMACITE_AT_THIS                                 = 11147,  -- You can infuse up to # atmacite at this time.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_INFUSED                              = 11148,  -- What will you do? Nothing for now. Infused: % (Lv.#) Infused: % (Lv.#) Infused: % (Lv.#) Purge atmacite. Infuse atmacite. Enrich atmacite.
        INFUSE_WHICH_ATMACITE_CRUOR_NONE_FOR_NOW_LV                           = 11149,  -- Infuse which atmacite? (Cruor: #) None for now. % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) Previous page. Next page.
        THE_LV_BESTOWS_THE_FOLLOWING_BONUSES                                  = 11150,  -- The % (Lv.#) bestows the following bonuses:
        INFUSING_THE_LV_REQUIRES_CRUOR                                        = 11151,  -- Infusing the % (Lv.#) requires # cruor.
        INFUSE_LV_YES_NO                                                      = 11152,  -- Infuse % (Lv.#)? Yes. No.
        REPLACE_LV_YES_NO                                                     = 11153,  -- Replace % (Lv.#)? Yes. No.
        EXPENDS_CRUOR_AND_IS_NOW_INFUSED_WITH_LV                              = 11154,  -- % expends # cruor and is now infused with % (Lv.#)!
        WHICH_ATMACITE_NONE_FOR_NOW_LV_LV_LV                                  = 11155,  -- [Infuse/Purge] which atmacite? None for now. % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#) % (Lv.#)
        PURGE_LV_YES_NO                                                       = 11156,  -- Purge % (Lv.#)? Yes. No.
        PURGES_THE_LV_INFUSING_LV_IN_ITS_PLACE                                = 11157,  -- % purges the % (Lv.#), infusing % (Lv.#) in its place. (Cruor expended: #)
        PURGE_LV_YES_NO_2                                                     = 11158,  -- Purge % (Lv.#)? Yes. No.
        HAS_BEEN_PURGED_OF_THE_LV                                             = 11159,  -- % has been purged of the % (Lv.#).
        YOU_DO_NOT_HAVE_ENOUGH_CRUOR_3                                        = 11160,  -- You do not have enough cruor.
        THE_ATMACITE_COULD_NOT_BE_INFUSED                                     = 11161,  -- The atmacite could not be infused...
        THE_ATMACITE_COULD_NOT_BE_PURGED                                      = 11162,  -- The atmacite could not be purged...
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_ANY_ATMACITE_CAPABLE_OF                            = 11163,  -- You do not possess any atmacite capable of enrichment.
        ENRICH_WHICH_ATMACITE_CRUOR_NONE_FOR_NOW_LV                           = 11164,  -- Enrich which atmacite? (Cruor: #) None for now. % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # % (Lv.#): # Previous page. Next page.
        ENRICHING_THE_WILL_PRODUCE_THE_FOLLOWING                              = 11165,  -- Enriching the % will produce the following:
        ENRICHING_THE_FROM_LEVEL_TO_LEVEL_REQUIRES_CRUOR                      = 11166,  -- Enriching the % from level # to level # requires # cruor.
        ENRICH_YES_NO                                                         = 11167,  -- Enrich %? Yes. No.
        YOUR_HAS_BEEN_ENRICHED_TO_LEVEL_CRUOR_EXPENDED                        = 11168,  -- Your % has been enriched to level #! (Cruor expended: #)
        THE_HAS_BEEN_ENRICHED_TO_ITS_MAXIMUM_LEVEL                            = 11169,  -- The % has been enriched to its maximum level!
        THE_ATMACITE_S_ENRICHMENT_LEVEL_FAILED_TO_RISE                        = 11170,  -- The atmacite's enrichment level failed to rise...
        READ_UP_ON_WHAT_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_VOIDWATCH                             = 11171,  -- Read up on what? Nothing for now. Voidwatch Ops. How to participate. %. Stratum abyssite. Alignment. Atmacite. Periapt.
        THE_VOIDWATCH_IS_A_FELLOWSHIP_OF_MEN_AND                              = 11172,  -- The Voidwatch is a fellowship of men and women come together to defend the world from extradimensional invaders called Voidwalkers. Driven only by an insatiable appetite for destruction, these fell horrors roam the space between dimensions, ever seeking to enter and plunge Vana'diel into chaos.
        FACED_WITH_THE_RISK_OF_MASS_INVASION_VOIDWATCH                        = 11173,  -- Faced with the risk of mass invasion, Voidwatch leaders devised a strategy wherein potential threats are preemptively neutralized. This act was made possible through the discovery of voidstones, magicked objects capable of rendering Voidwalkers visible to be summarily dispatched.
        SUCH_EFFORTS_TO_STEM_THE_RISE_OF_VOIDWALKERS                          = 11174,  -- Such efforts to stem the rise of Voidwalkers, collectively dubbed Voidwatch Operations, or Ops for short, take place in the vicinity of planar rifts--weak points in the fabric of space.
        A_SINGLE_PERSON_MAY_INITIATE_A_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION                    = 11175,  -- A single person may initiate a Voidwatch operation, at which time Voidwatcher status will be bestowed upon all qualifying party and alliance members, allowing them to commence battle with the target Voidwalker.
        VOIDWATCH_OPS_ARE_SUBJECT_TO_A_TIME_LIMIT                             = 11176,  -- Voidwatch Ops are subject to a time limit. Exceed this limit and Voidwatcher status will be revoked for all involved, bringing the confrontation to an end. Individuals straying too far from the site of battle, too, will find themselves relieved of the status.
        KNOW_ALSO_THAT_THOSE_WHO_TAKE_ON_THE                                  = 11177,  -- Know also that those who take on the burden of the Voidwatcher become temporarily isolated and unable to receive aid from the outside world. Such is the arduous nature of transdimensional encounters.
        INITIATING_A_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION_REQUIRES_A_VOIDSTONE_AS              = 11178,  -- Initiating a Voidwatch operation requires a voidstone, as well as a stratum abyssite attuned to a particular planar rift.
        ONLY_ONE_PERSON_NEEDS_TO_BE_IN_POSSESSION                             = 11179,  -- Only one person needs to be in possession of these objects for all party and alliance members to participate.
        HOWEVER_THERE_EXISTS_A_NUMBER_OF_PARTICIPATION_CONDITIONS             = 11180,  -- However, there exists a number of participation conditions that must be observed.
        WHEN_AN_OPERATION_COMMENCES_A_SINGLE_VOIDSTONE_WILL                   = 11181,  -- When an operation commences, a single voidstone will be expended for all who possess it. These combatants will have the opportunity to improve their spoils by manipulating spectral alignment values during battle.
        CONVERSELY_THOSE_NOT_POSSESSING_THEIR_OWN_VOIDSTONE_WILL              = 11182,  -- Conversely, those not possessing their own voidstone will be limited in the spoils they can obtain.
        THE_VOIDSTONE_IS_A_MAGICKED_OBJECT_WHICH_WHEN                         = 11183,  -- The voidstone is a magicked object which, when coupled with stratum abyssite, is capable of rendering Voidwalkers visible.
        ONLY_A_SINGLE_COMBATANT_NEED_POSSESS_A_VOIDSTONE                      = 11184,  -- Only a single combatant need possess a voidstone to allow all party and alliance members to participate in a Voidwatch operation. Those without one, however, will find their spoils limited in both quantity and quality.
        AS_A_SINGLE_VOIDSTONE_IS_AUTOMATICALLY_EXPENDED_WHEN                  = 11185,  -- As a single voidstone is automatically expended when the battle commences, it is recommended that you keep stock of your inventory.
        THOSE_WISHING_TO_OBTAIN_THE_STONES_SHOULD_SPEAK                       = 11186,  -- Those wishing to obtain the stones should speak to a Voidwatch officer, who is charged with issuing a set quantity at fixed intervals.
        STRATUM_ABYSSITE_ARE_DYNAMIC_STONES_CAPABLE_OF_EVOLUTION              = 11187,  -- Stratum abyssite are dynamic stones capable of evolution. By absorbing the energies emitted by felled Voidwalkers, they become attuned with other planar rifts.
        AFTER_DEFEATING_YOUR_QUARRY_PRESENT_YOUR_STONE_TO                     = 11188,  -- After defeating your quarry, present your stone to an atmacite refiner--specialists in the study of otherworld geology--to have its properties determined.
        STRATUM_ABYSSITE_GROWTH_OCCURS_INDEPENDENTLY_OF_VOIDSTONES_AND        = 11189,  -- Stratum abyssite growth occurs independently of voidstones, and the latter is not required to trigger development.
        EACH_DIMENSION_IS_COMPOSED_OF_ITS_OWN_EXISTENTIAL                     = 11190,  -- Each dimension is composed of its own existential spectrum to which objects of that world are aligned. The act of rendering a Voidwalker visible is essentially an act of aligning oneself to its existential spectrum.
        WHILE_VOIDWATCHERS_ARE_ABLE_TO_FOR_ALL_PRACTICAL                      = 11191,  -- While Voidwatchers are able to, for all practical purposes, interact with such creatures, they in fact fall short of full alignment. Symptoms of this imperfect state can be observed in the limited quantity and quality of spoils normally yielded by Voidwalkers.
        COMPENSATING_MEASURES_HOWEVER_EXIST_WHICH_ALLOW_COMBATANTS_TO         = 11192,  -- Compensating measures, however, exist which allow combatants to more closely attune themselves with their extradimensional foe. One such method involves the use of alignment-enhancing artifacts known as ascent items.
        ALIGNMENT_VALUES_RAISED_THROUGH_ASCENT_ITEMS_WILL_REMAIN              = 11193,  -- Alignment values raised through ascent items will remain in place until such time as a riftworn pyxis is opened at the end of a successful operation.
        THOSE_PARTICIPATING_IN_VOIDWATCH_OPS_ARE_RECOMMENDED_TO               = 11194,  -- Those participating in Voidwatch Ops are recommended to plan ahead in order to make effective use of ascent items.
        ALIGNMENT_VALUES_CAN_ALSO_BE_RAISED_IN_THE                            = 11195,  -- Alignment values can also be raised in the midst of battle by striking at enemy weaknesses, causing their existential attunement to shift to your advantage.
        BLOWS_CAN_BE_DEALT_WITH_ABILITIES_SUCH_AS                             = 11196,  -- Blows can be dealt with abilities such as weapon skills and magic spells, and your choice of weakness and the manner in which you strike it will determine which hue of the alignment spectrum is affected.
